						<summary>

						<p>This records a gift of 90 sheep by one Kaḍikāvaṉ Kaḷḷāṉ of the <hi rend="bold">Vīraśōḻa-teriñja-Kaikkōḷar</hi> (regiment) for burning a perpetual lamp in the temple of Tirukkaḻ kōṭṭattu-Paramasvāmi at Tirukkuḍamukkil. <hi rend="bold">‘Vīraśōḻa’</hi> was a title of <hi rend="bold">Parāntaka I.</hi> This may be a record of <hi rend="bold">Ariñjaya.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
